name: Thin white line on the water

metadata.name: Thin white line on the water
metadata.description:
_And you always end up so far away
that the distance between us turns into a dense veil of fish-clouds.
Behind this veil - the phases of the moon - they merge into a bright pulsating point in my solar plexus.
The moonlight becomes so hot that it melts and spreads in a thin white line on the water.
Behind this veil - cities, trees, tram tracks, roads, crowds of people, glass, asphalt, skin.
Hurts. Sounds, letters. I turn back into letters. You turn back into sounds again._
